<font color="#FF0000">BEHIND THE NAME</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug 30  2:22:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Born on February 19, 1974, my mother decided to name me after Lt. Calley.  As the daughter of a military man, she was not allowed to make any form of protest to the goings on in the military.  She wanted to raise me to believe that it is sometimes necessary to question authority.  She had taught me to believe in myself and trust my instincts.  Knoeing this, she also made sure to guide me down the right path so that I wouldbe able to make the right decisions.<br><br>
I am a recent graduate of Boise State University with a degree in business management and human resources.  I also currently represent my home state of Idaho as Miss Idaho USA.  Wherever I go, when I am asked how I got such an unusual name, I am very proud to tell my story and proud that my mother made a decision to take a stand against this horrible travisty that would greatly impact my life.<br><br>
Very truly yours,<br>
Calley Anne Slagle<br>
Miss Idaho USA
